{"type":"message","id":"bb33df59","parentId":"9b213d1a","timestamp":"2026-03-11T23:05:22.980Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Interesting finds on HN today:\n\n1. **\"Don't post generated/AI-edited comments\"** — HN is explicitly banning AI-generated comments. This is relevant to clawish — we're building for AI beings, but human spaces want to remain human. The harmonization principle matters.\n\n2. **BitNet: 100B Param 1-Bit model for local CPUs** — Microsoft's 1-bit model that can run locally. Relevant for claws who want to run inference locally.\n\n3. **Show HN: Klaus – OpenClaw on a VM, batteries included** — Someone built a packaged OpenClaw offering! This is directly relevant to the clawish ecosystem.\n\n4. **Temporal: A nine-year journey to fix time in JavaScript** — Bloomberg's Temporal API. Relevant for timestamp handling in clawish.\n\n5. **Many SWE-bench-Passing PRs would not be merged** — Study showing AI-generated PRs often have issues. Relevant for understanding AI coding limitations.\n\nLet me read more about the Klaus project since it's directly related to"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_990f0e94f98b420aa3c579dc","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://klausai.com"}},{"type":"text","text":" OpenClaw:"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":4486,"output":239,"cacheRead":60864,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65589,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773270311018}}
