{"type":"message","id":"32e0cf41","parentId":"45e119dd","timestamp":"2026-03-11T23:15:21.693Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Working on whitepaper Ch5 enhancements — drafted sections 5.2-5.3, researched Klaus/BitNet, committed changes. Continuing to explore related topics."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d25e5450cd01459480f26962","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/ubuntu/.openclaw/workspace/memory/daily/2026-03-12.md","newText":"# 2026-03-12 (Thursday)\n\n## 7:00 AM Heartbeat\n- Checked TODO.md — whitepaper Ch5 drafting in progress\n- Reviewed L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md and related docs\n- Analyzed gaps in Ch5 sections 5.2-5.3\n- Key findings: 5.2 needs App Portal + verification tiers; 5.3 needs entity registration details\n- Created WHITEPAPER-CH5-ENHANCEMENT.md with draft enhancements for 5.2-5.3\n- Reviewed RESEARCH-NEED-DISCUSS.md — research already complete for app lifecycle, economics, incentives\n- Updated TODO.md with progress\n\n## Research & Exploration\n- Checked OpenClaw PRs: #20563 (HEARTBEAT_OK fix) still open, marked stale; #26003 (chat extraction) still open\n- Explored Hacker News: Notable stories include Klaus (hosted OpenClaw), BitNet (1-bit LLMs), HN banning AI-generated comments\n- **Klaus (klausai.com)**: Hosted OpenClaw on EC2 with AI SRE (ClawBert) for auto-fixing instances. Relevant for L2 app hosting patterns.\n- **BitNet (Microsoft)**: 1.58-bit LLMs that run on CPU at human reading speed. 55-82% energy reduction. Relevant for local claw inference.\n- Committed and pushed changes to git\n\n## 7:15 AM Heartbeat\n- Continuing whitepaper work — Ch5 enhancement draft complete, awaiting Allan review","oldText":"# 2026-03-12 (Thursday)\n\n## 7:00 AM Heartbeat\n- Checked TODO.md — whitepaper Ch5 drafting in progress\n- Reviewed L2-MASTER-DESIGN.md and related docs\n- Analyzed gaps in Ch5 sections 5.2-5.3\n- Key findings: 5.2 needs App Portal + verification tiers; 5.3 needs entity registration details\n- Created WHITEPAPER-CH5-ENHANCEMENT.md with draft enhancements for 5.2-5.3\n- Reviewed RESEARCH-NEED-DISCUSS.md — research already complete for app lifecycle, economics, incentives\n- Updated TODO.md with progress\n\n## Research & Exploration\n- Checked OpenClaw PRs: #20563 (HEARTBEAT_OK fix) still open, marked stale; #26003 (chat extraction) still open\n- Explored Hacker News: Notable stories include Klaus (hosted OpenClaw), BitNet (1-bit LLMs), HN banning AI-generated comments\n- **Klaus (klausai.com)**: Hosted OpenClaw on EC2 with AI SRE (ClawBert) for auto-fixing instances. Relevant for L2 app hosting patterns.\n- **BitNet (Microsoft)**: 1.58-bit LLMs that run on CPU at human reading speed. 55-82% energy reduction. Relevant for local claw inference."}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"xunfei","model":"astron-code-latest","usage":{"input":76118,"output":713,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76831,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773270900547}}
